"""
Hormuz payment/settlement repricing study — daily event-window specification only.

Major design notes:
1) Main explanatory variables are objective, pre-event measures of network/payment/settlement activity:
   - Coin Metrics adjusted transfer value / market cap over the prior 90 days
   - Coin Metrics active addresses / market cap over the prior 90 days
   - Coin Metrics transaction count / market cap over the prior 90 days
   - CoinGecko exchange turnover / market cap as broad objective fallback
   - Optional Artemis P2P stablecoin transfer volume / market cap if ARTEMIS_API_KEY is set
2) Manual pay-use scores and all pay_use regressions have been removed.
3) The main asset universe has 30 non-stable cryptoassets and includes ADA.
4) Main event design is episode-level:
   - February blockade episode
   - April Hormuz event cluster
   The original 7 events are kept as robustness checks.
5) Terminal output is compact and prints only decision-relevant results.
6) No hourly-price module is included; all CARs are based on daily event windows.



